00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.300
- You know, so we're watching the story

00:00:02.300 --> 00:00:06.580
about the Toy Hall of Fame,
which is in Rochester.

00:00:06.580 --> 00:00:08.340
And we're seeing all the
toys that are being inducted

00:00:08.340 --> 00:00:09.660
and so everyone in the
office starts talking

00:00:09.660 --> 00:00:11.980
about their favorite
toys growing up, right?

00:00:11.980 --> 00:00:13.460
So some people are like "Oh yeah, no

00:00:13.460 --> 00:00:15.140
for me it was Shoots and Ladders,

00:00:15.140 --> 00:00:16.420
and for me it was the sled,

00:00:16.420 --> 00:00:18.027
and for me it was this, it was that."

00:00:18.027 --> 00:00:19.057
And then, the people were like,

00:00:19.057 --> 00:00:21.590
"What was your favorite,
favorite toy growing up?"

00:00:21.590 --> 00:00:22.800
And I was like, "Genuinely,

00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:25.854
my favorite toy growing up was a brick."

00:00:25.854 --> 00:00:26.687
(audience laughs)

00:00:26.687 --> 00:00:28.820
All right, which sounds crazy

00:00:29.690 --> 00:00:33.003
but, Spinny why do you
walk away like I'm a crazy?

00:00:33.003 --> 00:00:33.836
(audience laughs)

00:00:33.836 --> 00:00:34.930
like you literally walk away

00:00:34.930 --> 00:00:36.530
like I'm saying the wildest thing.

00:00:36.530 --> 00:00:38.630
No cause we, so what happened was no,

00:00:38.630 --> 00:00:41.700
we had, when we were growing up I'd live

00:00:41.700 --> 00:00:42.690
at my Gran's house in Soweto,

00:00:42.690 --> 00:00:44.020
and then what would happen is,

00:00:44.020 --> 00:00:45.380
a lot of kids didn't have toys,

00:00:45.380 --> 00:00:46.410
but it wasn't like a sad thing

00:00:46.410 --> 00:00:47.360
like "Oh, I don't have toys."

00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:48.870
It was like we'd play
with whatever we find.

00:00:48.870 --> 00:00:50.980
And so the most popular
thing little boys would play

00:00:50.980 --> 00:00:52.370
with was bricks, and your brick was,

00:00:52.370 --> 00:00:53.890
you'd play with it like a toy car.

00:00:53.890 --> 00:00:55.490
So you'd walk around the
neighborhood searching

00:00:55.490 --> 00:00:57.030
for the best brick, all right?

00:00:57.030 --> 00:00:57.880
'Cause the game you would play,

00:00:57.880 --> 00:00:59.110
we didn't put wheels on it or anything,

00:00:59.110 --> 00:01:00.083
like someone asked in the office,

00:01:00.083 --> 00:01:00.916
they're like, "Did you put wheels on?"

00:01:00.916 --> 00:01:02.720
No, there's no wheels, where
were we gonna find wheels?

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:04.226
If we have wheels, we
wouldn't have these problems.

00:01:04.226 --> 00:01:06.310
(audience laughs)
So we just took bricks,

00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:07.390
so you would find bricks,

00:01:07.390 --> 00:01:09.170
and then the game you'd
play is you'd drive around

00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:10.800
in the dirt with your brick car,

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:13.430
and then you would smash
into the other boys' bricks,

00:01:13.430 --> 00:01:16.020
and then if your brick was
the last brick standing,

00:01:16.020 --> 00:01:17.340
you won the game.

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:18.750
So, like all of us, it was like a mission.

00:01:18.750 --> 00:01:19.987
You're like, "Man, I gotta
find bricks, I gotta."

00:01:19.987 --> 00:01:22.320
You just walk around the
whole day, just searching

00:01:22.320 --> 00:01:24.290
for bricks, and there's this one brick

00:01:24.290 --> 00:01:26.450
that we had called a
face brick, all right?

00:01:26.450 --> 00:01:28.410
Which is basically like
a really beautiful brick

00:01:28.410 --> 00:01:29.843
that you can, you know bricks
that you don't plaster over?

00:01:29.843 --> 00:01:31.810
'Cause you have that as
the face of your house,

00:01:31.810 --> 00:01:33.190
that's why you would call
it the face brick, right?

00:01:33.190 --> 00:01:34.897
And so, that was like the dream brick.

00:01:34.897 --> 00:01:37.110
It was the most expensive brick, though.

00:01:37.110 --> 00:01:38.420
You couldn't, you'd find everyone

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:41.200
